Durban - A Pinetown resident has been hospitalised after being beaten with a crowbar during a house robbery on Wednesday night. Colonel Thembeka Mbele, a KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, said the victim was seated in the lounge with her family when she noticed three men in the yard just after 7pm. "They immediately opened the door and assaulted her. Her husband was also hit with a crowbar on the head. They both sustained injuries. The suspects stole a DSTV decoder, TV set, cell phones and other belongings before fleeing the scene in complainantâ€™s vehicle and their getaway vehicle. The matter is still under investigation,"Mbele said. The victims vehicle was later recovered abandoned in the Cato Manor area. The stolen items were not recovered. Charges of robbery and assault with intent to cause grievous bodily harm are being investigated by Pinetown SAPS. The Ashley Neighbourhood Watch provided trauma counselling for the family after the incident. Daily News